<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-07T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-07T10:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5561/23: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-07T18:00:00+03:00">February
                                    7, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 7—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>54. Your 27, February 6, 2 p.m., have notified Foreign Office as
                            instructed. Your 26, February 6, 1 p.m. As Captain <persName corresp="#p_NDR1">Nimmer</persName>’s orders provide for his
                            departure within the next few days I have requested <pb facs="0287" n="181" xml:id="pg_181"/> through the Foreign Office farewell
                            interview with <persName corresp="#p_VKE1">Voroshilov</persName> for
                            both <persName corresp="#p_NDR1">Nimmer</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_WTD1">White</persName> explaining in note that office of
                            Naval Attaché has been abolished and that latter is to be withdrawn.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WJC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>